Backport upstream PR #808 to bound Avahi simple protocol clients for
CVE-2025-59529.

The CVE describes two concrete problems: simple protocol clients are
accepted without enforcing CLIENTS_MAX, and once file descriptors are
exhausted, accept() errors can flood logs.  The patch addresses both:

- Adds a real global simple-client cap.
- Adds a per-UID cap using peer credentials.
- Refuses excess clients immediately and closes the accepted fd.
- Demotes EMFILE / ENFILE accept failures to debug logging.
- On Solaris, uses getpeerucred() so the per-UID simple-client limit is enforced instead of falling back to only the global client limit.

The patch has two intentional deltas from the upstream patch: Solaris
credential support and the review-driven RLIMIT_NOFILE handling.  Both are
portability changes.  These deltas will be offered upstream once the
upstream patch stabilizes.

Upstream status: https://github.com/avahi/avahi/pull/808

